# 1. Executive Overview

AFAT-X10-V2 represents the second-generation evolution of the AFAT aerodynamic architecture.

Where AFAT-X10 utilizes a centralized lower fuselage airflow channel, AFAT-X10-V2 expands the concept into a dual-sided atmospheric capture and venturi acceleration network integrated into the aircraft structure.

The objective is to transform portions of the airframe into active aerodynamic systems capable of:

* Capturing airflow
* Accelerating pressure streams
* Producing lift-support effects
* Enhancing stability
* Reducing drag
* Improving flight efficiency

